Distribution and ecology. The species is halobiontic and represents the meridional faunal element in the Palaearctic Region (
Szadziewski 1985
) or the Saharo-Arabian element (
Alwin-Kownacka et al. 2016
). It was usually collected on rivers in steppes and deserts (
Remm 1976
). It has been reported from Iraq (
Goetghebuer 1934 a
), Hungary (
Goetghebuer, 1934 b
), Spain (
Delécolle et al. 1997
), Slovakia (
Tothova & Knoz 2006
), Ukraine (Crimea), Russia (Rostov, southern Siberia), Azerbaijan , Tadjikistan , Kazakhstan , Iran , southern Siberia and Mongolia ( Remm 1976 , 1988 ). We are unable to confirm Remm’s (1976, 1988) reports of the species from northern China .
